for your guys's wedding.

378
00:12:33,290 --> 00:12:35,525
- That was the most beautiful day.
- Best day of my life.

379
00:12:35,559 --> 00:12:37,527
- Aw...
- BLAINE: It's crazy to think

380
00:12:37,561 --> 00:12:39,742
- that we almost followed right in your footsteps.
- KURT: Well, almost,

381
00:12:39,768 --> 00:12:42,031
and that would have been
a beautiful day, too,

382
00:12:42,066 --> 00:12:44,033
but, you know, it just...
it wasn't meant to be.

383
00:12:44,068 --> 00:12:45,126
Young and foolish.

384
00:12:45,152 --> 00:12:46,986
Hey, maybe you two guys
weren't meant to be,

385
00:12:47,012 --> 00:12:49,748
but, it's, like...
young, foolish? Come on.

386
00:12:49,774 --> 00:12:52,965
Are any of us ever
really ready for anything?

387
00:12:53,230 --> 00:12:54,778
No, I wasn't ready to lose your mom.

388
00:12:55,035 --> 00:12:57,881
And because of that we haven't
wasted one day since we met.

389
00:12:57,915 --> 00:12:59,816
That's right... it's been
a crazy adventure ever since.

390
00:12:59,850 --> 00:13:01,651
Uh-huh, it has. You're
gonna make mistakes,

391
00:13:01,685 --> 00:13:03,953
and that's okay... I have made so many.

392
00:13:03,988 --> 00:13:05,555
- Are you saying I'm one?
- You are not one of them.

393
00:13:05,589 --> 00:13:06,890
- You are one of the good things.
- Thank you.

394
00:13:06,924 --> 00:13:08,040
CAROLE: But you just have to take

395
00:13:08,066 --> 00:13:09,540
every second of every day

396
00:13:09,566 --> 00:13:10,933
and squeeze it as tight as you can.

397
00:13:11,428 --> 00:13:13,629
Just wring every last bit out of it.

398
00:13:13,764 --> 00:13:15,231
- Finn taught me that.
- Yep.

399
00:13:15,266 --> 00:13:16,633
Finn taught me that,
cancer taught me that,

400
00:13:16,667 --> 00:13:19,428
seeing you in that
hospital bed taught me that.

401
00:13:19,717 --> 00:13:21,404
Man, officiating a wedding

402
00:13:21,439 --> 00:13:23,173
- really puts you in a mood.
- Yeah, it does.

403
00:13:23,207 --> 00:13:25,408
- You just start thinking, and philosophizing...
- Get serious.

404
00:13:25,443 --> 00:13:27,510
- And-and "speechifying"... Excuse me.
- CAROLE: So go and, you know what?

405
00:13:27,545 --> 00:13:29,145
- We're gonna get you a beverage.
- We'll let you guys... All right, get me...

406
00:13:29,180 --> 00:13:30,447
- I'm not drunk.
- No, he's not.

407
00:13:30,481 --> 00:13:31,700
(sighs)

408
00:13:32,783 --> 00:13:34,818
Okay, Mercedes, I need
you to find a spider,

409
00:13:34,852 --> 00:13:36,194
'cause it's good luck to
put a spider on your dress.

410
00:13:36,220 --> 00:13:38,845
Um, and Tina, I need to find
some wine glasses to smash

411
00:13:38,871 --> 00:13:40,172
like the Jews do, 'cause
they have the best of luck.

412
00:13:40,324 --> 00:13:41,593
Oh, and, um, Rachel, I need you to

413
00:13:41,619 --> 00:13:43,586
find me a lizard to cross my path...

414
00:13:43,728 --> 00:13:45,303
Trust me, it's, like,
witch's lore, or something.

415
00:13:45,709 --> 00:13:47,464
Go! I need all the good
luck I can get, okay?

416
00:13:47,498 --> 00:13:49,032
I don't want to end up like Jack and Rose.

417
00:13:49,066 --> 00:13:50,433
Where the hell am I gonna find a lizard?

418
00:13:50,468 --> 00:13:51,668
Go, go, go.

419
00:13:51,702 --> 00:13:53,903
(sighs) Good luck, good luck, good luck.

420
00:13:55,239 --> 00:13:56,706
When I pictured my wedding day,

421
00:13:56,741 --> 00:13:59,142
I thought that I'd be the
most beautiful bride ever,

422
00:13:59,176 --> 00:14:00,643
but I was wrong.

423
00:14:00,678 --> 00:14:01,945
You are... you look amazing.

424
00:14:01,979 --> 00:14:03,373
Santana, what are you doing here?

425
00:14:03,399 --> 00:14:05,067
This is, like, the ultimate bad luck.

426
00:14:05,220 --> 00:14:07,576
God, a bride cannot see her
bride before the ceremony.

427
00:14:07,927 --> 00:14:09,953
Why are you trying to
sabotage this wedding?

428
00:14:09,987 --> 00:14:11,354
You know what?

429
00:14:11,389 --> 00:14:12,789
This was all adorable,

430
00:14:12,823 --> 00:14:14,576
but now I'm putting my foot down.

431
00:14:14,958 --> 00:14:16,893
Do you even know why a
groom couldn't see the bride

432
00:14:16,927 --> 00:14:17,961
before the wedding?

433
00:14:18,320 --> 00:14:19,195
Cannibalism?

434
00:14:19,230 --> 00:14:19,812
No.

435
00:14:20,031 --> 00:14:22,499
Dates back to arranged marriages.

436
00:14:22,533 --> 00:14:24,273
People thought that if the couple had time

437
00:14:24,299 --> 00:14:25,902
to see each other before the wedding,

438
00:14:25,936 --> 00:14:27,337
they would change their minds

439
00:14:27,371 --> 00:14:28,847
and bail on actually getting married.

440
00:14:29,571 --> 00:14:30,907
That's not us, okay?

441
00:14:30,941 --> 00:14:33,767
Because you love me, and I love you.

442
00:14:33,793 --> 00:14:36,262
And no silly superstitions
are gonna change that.

443
00:14:37,588 --> 00:14:38,988
Hey.

444
00:14:39,116 --> 00:14:41,165
I'm really sorry that I can't go an hour

445
00:14:41,191 --> 00:14:44,421
without seeing you, 'cause
I'll just miss you too much.

446
00:14:45,368 --> 00:14:46,698
And me and you?

447
00:14:47,142 --> 00:14:48,324
Rules don't apply to us.

448
00:14:48,618 --> 00:14:49,325
They never have.

449
00:14:49,360 --> 00:14:50,212
We make our own luck,

450
00:14:50,238 --> 00:14:53,040
so I say that it's good luck

451
00:14:53,186 --> 00:14:55,521
to kiss the bride before the
wedding because then we can have

452
00:14:55,547 --> 00:14:57,942
that kiss that we can't have in
front of our friends and family

453
00:14:57,968 --> 00:14:59,202
'cause they'd be too jealous.

454
00:14:59,236 --> 00:15:00,236
(sighs)

455
00:15:04,909 --> 00:15:06,309
- Come here.
- I agree.

456
00:15:14,285 --> 00:15:15,832
I love you so much.

457
00:15:16,787 --> 00:15:19,255
(sighs) But so does this
mean I don't have to wear

458
00:15:19,290 --> 00:15:20,757
